@itemize
@item
@strong{table-name} specifies the name of the DB table.
@end itemize

@itemize
@item
@strong{defs} is a list to define the type of columns. For example:
@end itemize

@verbatim
'((name varchar 10) (age integer) (email varchar 20))
@end verbatim

@itemize
@item
@code{#:if-exists?} has two kinds of possible options:
@itemize
@item
'@strong{overwrite} and '@strong{drop}, which will overwrite the existing table.
@item
'@strong{ignore} means to ignore the table when it already exists.
@end itemize

@item
@code{#:primary-keys} specifies the primary keys in the created table.
@end itemize

@itemize
@item
@code{#:engine} specifies the DB engine. It depends on what dbd you chose.
@end itemize

